{"title":"WTC Adds New Single Speed Parts Incl. Steel Lockring, Colorful Cogs + Bosch eBike Rings!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/wtc-adds-new-single-speed-parts-incl-steel-lockring-colorful-cogs-bosch-ebike-rings/","date":1712069890000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_6-800x533.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" alt=\"Single Speed cog on freehub with WTC spacer kit\" /></p>\n<p>Single-speeders rejoice. Wolf Tooth Components is adding to their collection of 1×1 specific parts including a new lockring, spacer kit, and new colors of SS cogs. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-LCKRNG.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-LCKRNG-800x800.jpg\" alt=\"Stainless steel cassette lockring single speed\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-LCKRNG-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-LCKRNG-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-LCKRNG-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-LCKRNG-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-LCKRNG-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-LCKRNG.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-SPCR-LCK-KIT.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-SPCR-LCK-KIT-800x800.jpg\" alt=\"WTC SS lockring kit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-SPCR-LCK-KIT-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-SPCR-LCK-KIT-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-SPCR-LCK-KIT-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-SPCR-LCK-KIT-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-SPCR-LCK-KIT-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SS-SPCR-LCK-KIT.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth_SS cogs and spacers kit_4\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth_SS-cogs-and-spacers-kit_4-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you need to adapt those multi-speed HG freehubs to single-speed, you’ll need a Single Speed Spacer Kit. WTC now offers a kit that is compatible with any 10 or 11-speed HG freehub body, which includes two 1.5mm, three 5mm, and one 15mm aluminum spacers. With this combination, you can achieve a 45, 47.5, 49, 52, or 55mm chainline.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The kit will be sold as spacers only for $29.99 or with their new stainless steel lockring for $44.95. Currently, you can’t buy the lockring separately. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-ORG-COG20.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-ORG-COG20-800x800.jpg\" alt=\"orange SS cog\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-ORG-COG20-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-ORG-COG20-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-ORG-COG20-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-ORG-COG20-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-ORG-COG20-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-ORG-COG20.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-GLD-COG17.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-GLD-COG17-800x800.jpg\" alt=\"gold SS cog\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-GLD-COG17-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-GLD-COG17-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-GLD-COG17-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-GLD-COG17-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-GLD-COG17-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-GLD-COG17.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-COG17_02.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-COG17_02-800x800.jpg\" alt=\"black SS cog\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-COG17_02-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-COG17_02-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-COG17_02-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-COG17_02-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-COG17_02-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-COG17_02.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-BLU-COG18_02.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-BLU-COG18_02-800x800.jpg\" alt=\"blue SS cog\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-BLU-COG18_02-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-BLU-COG18_02-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-BLU-COG18_02-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-BLU-COG18_02-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-BLU-COG18_02-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-BLU-COG18_02.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-PRP-COG18_02.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-PRP-COG18_02-800x800.jpg\" alt=\"purple SS cog\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-PRP-COG18_02-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-PRP-COG18_02-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-PRP-COG18_02-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-PRP-COG18_02-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-PRP-COG18_02-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_AL-SS-PRP-COG18_02.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_SST-SS-COG18_01.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_SST-SS-COG18_01-800x800.jpg\" alt=\"stainless steel SS cog\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_SST-SS-COG18_01-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_SST-SS-COG18_01-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_SST-SS-COG18_01-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_SST-SS-COG18_01-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_SST-SS-COG18_01-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_SST-SS-COG18_01.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the cog side, WTC is adding orange and gold to their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-rolls-new-aluminum-single-speed-cogs-plus-orange-gc42/\" target=\"_blank\">current line up of aluminum cogs</a> which includes black, blue, green, and purple. They also offer a silver stainless steel cog for added durability. Aluminum cogs sell for $54.95 while the SS version is $79.95. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Bosch eBike Chainrings</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BNP-7822_1200x.jpg.webp\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BNP-7822_1200x.jpg-800x533.webp\" alt=\"Bosch ebike Ring\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BNP-7822_1200x.jpg-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BNP-7822_1200x.jpg-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BNP-7822_1200x.jpg-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BNP-7822_1200x.jpg-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BNP-7822_1200x.jpg-720x480.webp 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BNP-7822_1200x.jpg.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_BG4-32-B_01_1200x.jpg.webp\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_BG4-32-B_01_1200x.jpg-800x800.webp\" alt=\"Bosch chainring WTC\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_BG4-32-B_01_1200x.jpg-800x800.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_BG4-32-B_01_1200x.jpg-297x297.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_BG4-32-B_01_1200x.jpg-120x120.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_BG4-32-B_01_1200x.jpg-768x768.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/WT_BG4-32-B_01_1200x.jpg.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, WTC is expanding their chainring selection with a direct mount version for Bosch eBikes. Available in 32 or 34t and in Drop-Stop B or Strop-Stop ST tooth profiles, the chainrings will cover most 9, 10, 11, and 12 speed chains. Compatible with Boost and Super Boost bikes running the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bosch-performance-line-sx-ebike-motor/\" target=\"_blank\">Bosch Gen 4 ebike motor</a>, the rings have a 55mm chainline, and a claimed weight of 98-105g. Any style sells for $89.95. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/products/direct-mount-chainrings-bosch-e-bike-motor?variant=39966845141027\" target=\"_blank\">wolftoothcomponents.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wtc-adds-new-single-speed-parts-incl-steel-lockring-colorful-cogs-bosch-ebike-rings/\">WTC Adds New Single Speed Parts Incl. Steel Lockring, Colorful Cogs + Bosch eBike Rings!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"ed9059c627627ec091e18a831a60fb692b276762e374c856e3a6f59c8ee5bd50","category":"Cycling"}